HEADWORD: Anethol
<hw>An"e*thol</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aneth</ets>um (see <er>Anise</er>) + <ets>-ol</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance obtained from the volatile oils of
anise, fennel, etc., in the form of soft shining scales; -- called also
<altname>anise camphor</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

